The paper deals with object and relation reasoning in structured scenes, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for this purpose also makes it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of memory mechanisms, which is a topic studied in neural networks (cs.NE).
